{"ts":"2026-06-26T06:24:14.377Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Designing AI Academy Sections**\n\nI'm now sketching out the structure for the AI Academy workspace. I've decided on an `InnerPageShell` wrapper and an `InnerPageHero` with a breadcrumb. The overview section will use a MotionReveal grid. I am developing an interactive curriculum console with tabs for \"Technical AI Engineering,\" \"Operations & Risk Governance,\" and \"Executive & Strategic Stewardship\" each with specific tracks.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T06:24:16.450Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Detailing Curriculum Content**\n\nI am now focusing on the curriculum details. My current vision involves showcasing core modules and emphasizing hands-on labs like \"Local Sandbox Execution\" and \"Sovereign eBPF Shield Setup.\" I'm also planning a mock execution preview terminal to demonstrate a CLI sequence, like `gff academy test --agent=topology-1`, making the learning path feel realistic and high-tech. I am using a `BentoGrid` and `BentoCard` setup to clearly describe structural enablement pillars, like \"Sovereign Sandboxes,\" \"Continuous Assessments,\" and \"Governance Playbooks.\" A 4-stage adoption timeline will illustrate the enterprise rollout, and a premium CTA at the bottom will link to `/contact` for an onboarding workshop.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T06:24:17.995Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Incorporating Lucide Icons**\n\nI'm now integrating Lucide icons into the AI Academy design, pulling in ones like `BookOpen`, `Shield`, and `Workflow`. I'm happy to see that Lucide React is already in use, and I'm importing icons directly from `lucide-react`. I will ensure a premium and cohesive design across all pages. The goal is to make all three pages have a distinct look. I'm focusing on a clean and robust layout for the AI Academy page and will subsequently design the University OneVerse page. The third page will be an extension of the University OneVerse page.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T06:24:19.230Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Developing OneVerse Interface**\n\nI'm now building the University OneVerse platform page. I've defined its key description and breadcrumbs. My design now features a top bar narrative grid that outlines the shortcomings of legacy systems and positions OneVerse as the sovereign solution. The core of my current focus is the interactive portal interface, which will simulate the experience for different users: students, faculty/researchers, and campus operations. I'm exploring specific interactions for each user type within this simulated environment.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T06:24:20.767Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining Assessment Mesh**\n\nI am now conceptualizing the \"Assessment Mesh\" platform page. I'm focusing on user interactions, including automated course scheduling and facility analytics under Administration & Registry. I'm imagining a dynamic portal interface for different roles, showing current system states, agent protocols, and a simulated process console. I'm using Bento cards to showcase the technical architecture, like Federated Knowledge Base and Sovereign Compute Guardrails. I'm also planning a structured timeline for institution-wide integration and a premium CTA to consult with a GFF Academic Systems Architect.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T06:24:22.529Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Implementing Assessment Calculator**\n\nI'm now implementing the interactive assessment calculator for the \"Assessment Mesh\" page. I've designed the `InnerPageHero` with structured diagnostic category and a GFF Assessment Mesh Engine title. The plan is to include a multi-agent readiness validation framework, and a dynamic metric panel. Users will have sliders for Sovereign Compliance, Data Density, Compute Scalability, and Workflow Automation, and I will display a real-time GFF Sovereign AI Readiness Index. I am planning on adding dynamic diagnostic warnings and recommendations based on the slider adjustments.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
